criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  American Society of Anesthesiology (ASA) I-II, undergoing selective surgery for
             hypospadias repair.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  a history of developmental delay or mental retardation, which could make observational
             pain intensity assessment outside the norm;

          -  a history of central nervous system diseases;

          -  a known or suspected coagulopathy;

          -  a known allergy to any of the study drugs;

          -  abnormalities of the sacrum and any signs of infection at the site of the proposed
             caudal block.
